'''Besfort Zeneli''' (born 21 November 2002) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|football]]er who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==

=== IF Elfsborg ===
On 6 January 2022, Zeneli signed his first professional contract with [[Allsvenskan]] side [[IF Elfsborg]] after agreeing to a two-year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://elfsborg.se/2022/01/06/zeneli-och-widell-skriver-a-lagskontrakt/|title=Zeneli och Widell skriver A-lagskontrakt|trans-title=Zeneli and Widell sign A team contracts|language=Swedish|publisher=[[IF Elfsborg]]|date=6 January 2022}}</ref> On 21 July 2022, he was named as an IF Elfsborg substitute for the first time in a [[2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League qualifying phase and play-off round (Main Path)#Second qualifying round|2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League second qualifying round]] against [[Molde FK|Molde]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=IFElfsborg1904|author-link=IF Elfsborg|number=1550133523847061504|language=Swedish|date=21 July 2022|title=Avspark om 60 minuter – här är dagens startelva {{!}} Substitutioner: Valdimarsson, Jarjué, Holmén, Hult, Söderberg, Zeneli, Baidoo, Qasem, Okkels, Bernhardsson, Gudjohnsen, Aga {{!}} #vitillsammans #elfsborg #borås|trans-title=Kick-off in 60 minutes – here is today's starting line-up {{!}} Substitutions: Valdimarsson, Jarjué, Holmén, Hult, Söderberg, Zeneli, Baidoo, Qasem, Okkels, Bernhardsson, Gudjohnsen, Aga {{!}} #wetogether #elfsborg #borås}}</ref> His debut with IF Elfsborg came seven days later in the 2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League second qualifying round again against Molde after coming on as a substitute at 73rd minute in place of [[Michael Baidoo]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=IFElfsborg1904|author-link=IF Elfsborg|number=1552719615658266627|language=Swedish|date=28 July 2022|title=Substitutioner: 73' {{!}} Tre byten i IFE!|trans-title=Substitutions: 73' {{!}} Three changes in IFE!}}</ref> On 11 September 2022, Zeneli made his league debut in a 2–0 away win against [[GIF Sundsvall]] after coming on as a substitute at last minutes again in place of Michael Baidoo.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=IFElfsborg1904|author-link=IF Elfsborg|number=1568975665449570305|language=Swedish|date=11 September 2022|title=90+2' Byte {{!}} Besfort Zeneli ersätter Michael Baidoo {{!}} #GIF 0–2 #IFE|trans-title=90+2' Change {{!}} Besfort Zeneli replaces Michael Baidoo {{!}} #GIF 0–2 #IFE}}</ref>

=== Royale Union Saint-Gilloise ===
On 13 January 2026 Zeneli joined Belgian club [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-01-13 |title=Swedish metronome Besfort Zeneli signs for Union |url=https://rusg.brussels/en/news/swedish-metronome-besfort-zeneli-signs-union |access-date=2026-01-13 |website=RUSG |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
===Kosovo===
Zeneli was eligible to represent two countries on international level, either [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] or [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]]. On 18 October 2021, Zeneli declared through an interview for [[Koha Ditore]] that he is waiting for a call-up from [[Football Federation of Kosovo]] to represent [[Kosovo]] at the [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|under-21 level]] and that he had refused to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Sweden national youth football team|youth level]] even though he had the opportunity to choose.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.koha.net/sport/293025/19-gola-ne-17-ndeshje-vellai-i-arber-zenelit-po-e-pret-kosoven/|title=19 gola në 17 ndeshje, vëllai i Arbër Zenelit po e pret Kosovën|trans-title=19 goals in 17 games, the brother of Arbër Zeneli is waiting for Kosovo|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Koha Ditore]]|date=18 October 2021}}</ref> On 15 September 2022, Zeneli received a call-up from Kosovo U21 for a training camp held in [[Antalya]], Turkey and for the hybrid [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly match]] against [[Greenland national football team|Greenland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegrafi.com/toverlani-publikon-listen-e-perfaqesueses-u21-te-kosoves-per-synimet-varet-vetem-nga-shorti/|title=Tovërlani publikon listën e Përfaqësueses U21 të Kosovës: Për synimet varet vetëm nga shorti|trans-title=Tovërlani publishes the list of the Kosovo national under-21 team: For objectives, it depends only on the draw|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|date=15 September 2022}}</ref>

On 18 March 2023, Zeneli received again a call-up from Kosovo U21 for the friendly matches against [[Moldova national under-21 football team|Moldova]] and [[Turkey national under-21 football team|Turkey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/kosova-u21-luan-dy-miqesore-ne-turqi-kjo-eshte-lista-e-futbollisteve-te-ftuar-nga-toverlani/|title=Kosova U21 luan dy miqësore në Turqi, kjo është lista e futbollistëve të ftuar nga Tovërlani|trans-title=Kosovo U21 plays two friendlies in Turkey, this is the list of footballers invited from Tovërlani|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=18 March 2023}}</ref> His official debut with Kosovo U21 came six days later in the friendly match against Moldova after coming on as a substitute in place of [[Veton Tusha]].

===Sweden===
On 9 September 2024, Zeneli declined a call-up to [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo U21]] and announced him deciding to represent Sweden on an international level instead,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/sverige/zeneli-byter-till-sveriges-landslag/|title=Zeneli byter till Sveriges landslag|trans-title=Zeneli joins the Swedish national team|language=sv|website=Fotbollskanalen.se|date=3 September 2024}}</ref> due to the alleged mistreatment of him and his brother by the Football Federation of Kosovo.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nacionale.com/sport/avni-zeneli-besforti-ka-thene-se-me-dite-qe-karriera-perfundon-ketu-nuk-shkon-me-te-kosova|title=Avni Zeneli: Besforti ka thënë se me ditë që karriera përfundon këtu nuk shkon më te Kosova|trans-title=Avni Zeneli: Besfort has said that the day his career ends here, he will no longer go to Kosovo|language=sq|publisher=[[Nacionale]]|date=6 October 2024}}</ref>

On 24 February 2025, Zeneli's request to switch allegiance to Sweden was accepted by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|publisher=[[FIFA]]|access-date=24 February 2025}}</ref> On 12 March 2025, he accepted a call-up to the [[Sweden men's national football team|senior team]] for the [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly matches]] against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] and [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2025/03/zeneli-far-chansen-olsen-tillbaka/|title=Zeneli får chansen – Olsen tillbaka|trans-title=Zeneli gets the chance – Olsen is back|language=Swedish|publisher=[[Swedish Football Association]]|date=12 March 2025}}</ref> He made his full international debut on 22 March 2025, playing for 45 minutes in a friendly 1–0 loss against Luxembourg before being replaced by [[Yasin Ayari]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Luxembourg vs. Sweden |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/luxemburg-sverige-landskamper-herr-senior/6155569/ |website=SvFF}}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Zeneli was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born and raised in Sweden, Zeneli is of Kosovo Albanian origin from Selac, a village near [[Mitrovica, Kosovo|Mitrovica]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kallxo.com/ndryshe/arber-zeneli-djaloshi-me-origjine-nga-mitrovica-qe-po-ben-krenare-te-gjithe-foto/|title=Arbër Zeneli, djaloshi me origjinë nga Mitrovica që po bën krenarë të gjithë (FOTO)|trans-title=Arbër Zeneli, the boy with origin from Mitrovica that is making everyone proud (PHOTO)|quote=I lindur më 25 shkurt të vitit 1995, në qytetin Säter të Suedisë, Arbëri i ka prindërit nga Kosova, konkretisht nga Selaci i Mitrovicës|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Kallxo]]|date=21 November 2018}}</ref> He is the younger brother of [[List of Kosovo international footballers|Kosovo international]] [[Arbër Zeneli]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://korrespodenti.com/sporti/njihuni-me-besfortin-vellain-e-arber-zenelit-qe-pritet-ta-pushtoje-boten-e-futbollit/|title=Njihuni me Besfortin, vëllain e Arbër Zenelit që pritet ta 'pushtojë' botën e futbollit|trans-title=Meet Besfort, the brother of Arbër Zeneli who is expected to 'conquer' the world of football|language=Albanian|website=korrespodenti.com|date=13 October 2019|archive-date=15 July 2023|access-date=30 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230715100627/https://korrespodenti.com/sporti/njihuni-me-besfortin-vellain-e-arber-zenelit-qe-pritet-ta-pushtoje-boten-e-futbollit/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

